rled. The street was silent behind thick dark-blue curtains. Little by little his thoughts resumed their mysterious course. The nutcracker cracking one hollow second after another, came to a full meaty one again. An indistinct sound like the echo of some remote ovation met the appearance of a new eidolon.

A fingernail scraped, tapped.

'What is it? What do you want?'

No answer. Smooth silence. Then an audible dimple. Then silence again.

He opened the door. She was standing there in her nightg